##MOM, why don't you go to Wuhan?

Micro-signal Yeguangbeifukan

Function introduction the supplement of Xinmin Evening News, founded on May 1,1946, is the oldest comprehensive supplement of Chinese newspapers.

Experience such a crisis event, the child will have a great impact on the young mind, but also can be a child's psychological growth opportunities.

Even I, a paramedic, was upset by COVID-19 pneumonia. While constantly brushing the progress of the epidemic, real-time reports, mood with the number of ups and downs, while worrying about buying masks, food, fidgety. Although we do not yet need a professional on the front line, but I can not stop on the front-line compatriots of gratitude and concern, always think about what you can do but not.

In the midst of such mixed feelings, it was hard for me to stay at home with my daughter and be at peace with her. As I watched the progress of the outbreak, the seven-year-old leaned over and read the names and numbers carefully, asking me what I meant by "confirmed" and "suspected. ". While my husband and I were discussing the latest developments in the epidemic and talking about our colleagues'flight to Wuhan, I didn't notice that my daughter was listening.

Until she suddenly asked me: "Mom, why don't you go to Wuhan? " I was speechless, a little laugh and cry, the child is a child, simply do not understand the disease and death is what it is. Looking at her serious, worried and confused look, I realized that we needed to talk.

I gently asked her: "Well, there are many doctors all over the country uncle and aunt have gone to Wuhan for support, there is no need for my mother to help. Why do you want my mother to go to Wuhan? "

Daughter very sincerely said: "because the mother to beat the virus, is Superman! "! So I don't get scared. There's so many things I can't figure out. "That's when I realized that since the outbreak, I've been so preoccupied that I've completely ignored the child's feelings, and she has all sorts of feelings of fear and worry and confusion. I asked her to use her hands to indicate how big she was afraid of, like a quail egg, an egg, an ostrich egg, or a dinosaur egg, she said. I said my own fears were the size of an egg. She was a little surprised that her mother's fear was as big as mine! I said yes, there are more eggs! Mother's worry like quail eggs, angry like pigeon eggs, confidence like ostrich eggs... ... We said and gestured, the daughter laughed happily. "Such a strange virus, so many people sick, we will have fear, worry, confusion, everyone will have, this is a very normal reaction. " I gently touched her head.

Then I found videos and picture books about what a virus is, and how to prevent infectious diseases, and I studied with my daughter, and I asked her a few questions in her favorite quiz format, and I got her a little prize. I told her that protecting herself from illness would actually help others, and I gave her a special task to supervise her grandparents while they went out to wear masks. My daughter felt very energetic for a while. She even did her homework seriously.

If you have children, be aware of their emotional reactions. Experience such a crisis event, the child will have a great impact on the young mind, but also can be a child's psychological growth opportunities. What you need to do is listen carefully to your child's feelings, let him or her learn to accept his or her emotions, let go of anxiety and fear in moderation, communicate patiently, let him or her understand and learn how to protect and encourage positive action, helping people makes them feel powerful. At the same time, as far as possible to ensure a normal life, to maintain the original schedule, to ensure adequate sleep and healthy diet, which are conducive to the child's mental and physical health. (the writer is a clinical psychologist of Sun Yat-sen Hospital affiliated to Fudan University.)
